Currently when you click "Merge" in a Pull Request, you get a message like below

{code}
Merged in userOrOrganization/branch (pull request #)

The title of the pull request

Approved-by: Some name and email
{code}

I don&#x27;t need the extra information of title or approved-by. I also prefer present tense verbs in my commit messages. So I&#x27;d much rather be able to change the default message to

{code}
Merge in userOrOrganization/branch (pull request #)
{code}

This would also be useful if people want to add more detail to a merge or reorganize it

